One of the students abducted by bandits who attacked the Federal Government College, Birnin Yauri, in Kebbi State, has been killed. Abubakar AbdulKadir, the deputy force commander of the joint task force in the north-west, disclosed this to reporters on Friday.  He, however, added that five others including four students and a teacher were rescued during a gun battle with the bandits. SaharaReporters had earlier reported that a female student of the school, who escaped the attack on the school on Thursday, says she doesn’t think the gunmen are Nigerians. See Also






